Italian Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  may replace  Eni SpA  Chief Executive Officer Paolo Scaroni, whose term ends in April, amid disagreements over its
gas contracts in Russia, daily  la Repubblica  reported, without
saying how it got the information.  State-controlled Eni is seeking to renegotiate natural gas
contracts with Russiaâ€™s OAO Gazprom, the newspaper said. Eni is
also carrying out a feasibility study of the South Stream gas
